**PROMPT:**

```
Create a McKinsey-grade Hebrew RTL presentation based on the attached instruction document "AI-Strategy-Presentation-Instructions.md".

EXECUTION REQUIREMENTS:
1. First read the mckinsey-presentation skill at /mnt/skills/user/mckinsey-presentation/SKILL.md
2. Then read the base pptx skill at /mnt/skills/public/pptx/SKILL.md and its dependencies (html2pptx.md, css.md)
3. Follow the html2pptx workflow exactly

BUILD PROCESS:
1. Extract html2pptx library
2. Create mckinsey-rtl.css file using the CSS provided in Part ג of the instructions
3. Create 11 HTML slide files (slide01.html through slide11.html) following the exact content, structure, and visual specifications in Part ב
4. Create build-presentation.js script
5. Run the build script to generate the PPTX
6. Validate visually: convert to PDF → images → inspect each slide for RTL issues, text cutoff, overlap
7. Fix any issues and regenerate until all slides pass validation
8. Deliver the final PPTX file

CRITICAL CONSTRAINTS:
- All text must be Hebrew RTL with Assistant font
- Every slide title must be an Action Title (complete sentence with insight)
- Use the exact color palette defined in the instructions
- Include all data points and sources as specified
- Slide dimensions: 960×540px (16:9)

OUTPUT: A polished, presentation-ready PPTX file named "AI-Strategy-Law-Faculty.pptx"
```

